popular_dishes: Fried Chicken, Shrimp Po Boy, Fried Oyster, Oyster Po Boy, Clam Chowder, Seafood Gumbo, Red Beans and Rice, Fried Shrimp, Catfish Po Boy, Fish and Chips, Fried Catfish, Single Po Boy Sandwich, Gulf Shrimp, Soft Shell Crab, Fish Tacos, Baja Shrimp Tacos, Chicken Po Boy, Chicken Tenders, Hot Sausage
address: 33 The Embarcadero Ste 100 San Francisco, CA 94133
about_business:
speciality:
Welcome to Queen's Louisiana Po-Boy Cafe, the original, premier and authentic Po-Boy Cafe in the San Francisco Bay Area. Come and enjoy our unique, over stuffed sandwiches and specialties that originated in the heart of New Orleans. At our cafe, you will enjoy the best Creole and Cajun dishes native to Southwestern Louisiana. 

As our name implies, we specialize in Po-Boys, the original Louisiana sandwich.  Our sandwiches are served on a Louisiana-style, light and crusty French Pistolet (baguette).  Our Pistolet are shipped directly to us from New Orleans, LA.  We specialize in authentic products such as our Gulf Shrimp and catfish, Louisiana Community Coffee, Zaps Potato Chips and Abita Bear.

We also do catering! Queen's Louisiana Po-Boy Cafe would love to cater your next event or party. Call us for information.

historyText:
Louisiana cuisine is at the heart of our unique culture created by the fusion of African, Native American and European Ancestry.  Here at Queen's, we aspire to embody the true principles of Louisiana food by using authentic products and fresh ingredients.

businessOwnerBio:
So come and join us!  We've created an atmosphere of warmth and Southern hospitality that is definitely unique with emphasis on the culture of Louisiana. Join us and share the heritage of Louisiana!  You are guaranteed to enjoy big flavors and original spices and most of all, the unsurpassed rustic sandwich.

speciality:
Dalida is a restaurant that is inspired by the genuine hospitality, fresh ingredients, familiar flavors, and deep culture of the Eastern Mediterranean. It's an upscale, full-service restaurant that offers fun luxury, elements of surprise, and the comfort of nostalgia. The atmosphere and vibe is elegant and confident yet relaxed. The restaurant is in the Presidio National Park, on the South Western corner of the Main Parade Lawn in the Presidio in a corner location. The front porch overlooks a beautiful lawn stretching all the way to Alcatraz. The restaurant features a main dining room, a private dining room, and a beautiful kitchen counter with windows on both sides.

historyText:
We are a husband and wife operating a pop-up restaurant and catering service, which we established after moving to San Francisco from New York. Between the two of us, we worked at 5 out of the worlds 50 best restaurants. These include Saison, Blue Hill at Stone Barns, Le Bernardin, Eleven Madison Park and Mugaritz. We are now cooking Istanbul-themed Middle Eastern Food. Sayat is from Istanbul.

businessOwnerBio:
We have been cooking in fine dining for many years and always noticed that Middle Eastern flavors get neglected and misunderstood. Prior to our arrival in San Francisco, we did a restaurant work trip that included 25 restaurants and 18 cities in the United States. We noticed, we can do something great with a blank canvas. Here we are with Istanbul Modern and enjoying every moment of the journey.

about_business:
speciality:
Welcome to Marcella's Lasagneria & Cucina, your local ambassador of fast- food, with a slow- food mentality! We are proposing a fresh take on classic, Italian favorites with the art of Lasagna making at the heart of our operation. Marcella's Lasagneria & Cucina aims to be your solution to making all-natural, fresh, and easy comfort food accessible to your family and friends at all times. We can even accommodate reservations for groups of 6 or more! 

We offer fresh varieties of Lasagna, flatbread pizzas, panini, salads and soups to feed your soul any day of the week; available here or even by arranging a delivery! As a family owned and operated business, we understand the demand on time that our modern lives impose, and we aim to partner with you to uphold a standard in food that is achievable for all. 

Nothing satisfies more completely than a piping hot portion of home made lasagna, a belief shared by many. Come visit us at our Dogpatch/Potrero location eat in the moment, order to-go, or pick-up for family events, Lunch time meetings, and much more! We're always happy to see you.

historyText:
As a family, we have been in the food business for the past 25 years in San Francisco. We like to think that our journey is coming full circle with our latest creation. We started over 20 years ago with a small cafe/restaurant that grew into a successful catering operation. As that chapter closed and others opened, we have successfully created all natural and organic  Italian food, product lines for local markets and Whole Foods Markets Northern California. With the desire to focus on our family operation and our passion for serving food in the moment, we are returning to our roots and re-opening our cafe /storefront in the Potrero/Dogpatch district. We look forward to seeing old friends and neighbors and meeting new ones as well. We hope you'll stop by, say hello, and enjoy the traditional Italian specialties we make for you!

businessOwnerBio:
Chef Massimo comes from the region of Abruzzo, in Southern Italy on the coast of the Adriatic. He grew up in the small, mountainside town of Fallo, a picturesque village on the outskirts of the National Park of Abruzzo. This particular region and even town is home to a number of great chefs in Italy, Europe, and other parts of the world. Chef Massimo is the Son of a great chef, and has carried on this legacy with extensive training throughout  Europe, experience in Canada and finally the United States, where he now resides in San Francisco, Ca. For more on Chef Massimo's professional career, check out his LinkedIn profile.

about_business:
speciality:
ABACÁ is a contemporary Filipino-Californian restaurant, showcasing the beauty and vibrance of Filipino culture and cuisine.  This family-owned restaurant has been a years-long journey in the making, compiling generations old family recipes, using the best ingredients Northern California has to offer, executed with skill and passion, honed in the kitchens of some of San Francisco's most beloved restaurants.  

ABACÁ located in San Francisco's Fisherman's Wharf neighborhood, is the sister restaurant of Pinoy Heritage,  2018 Pop-Up of the Year and two-time San Francisco Chronicle Top 100 Restaurants, and the second concept from Chef Francis Ang, San Francisco Chronicle Rising Star Chef.  

ABACÁ is open for dinner Mon-Sat from 5 - 9pm. Reservations recommended. ABACÁ Panaderia open Wed-Sun from 7am - 2:30pm, features fresh baked pastries, ensaymada, and espresso drinks from Oakland's Mr. Espresso.  All goods offered on a first come, first served basis.  No call ahead orders at this time.

Francesco is from Calabria (the tip of the toe of Italy) and his goal is to bring to the table the same flavor that he had back home. businessOwnerBio: I moved to San Francisco in 1999, and I worked in North Beach, managing different restaurants there. I finally got to the point where I was ready for my own restaurant and I find this wonderful little location in the heart of a colorful and happy neighborhood: The Castro.
I reached to the best employees that had worked with me in the past and I started my little dream.

historyText:
Opened Dec 1, the owner of  "Uncle Boy's" was irate about the fact that there was no fast no frills burger restaurant on the balboa strip of the Inner Richmond District of San Francisco. Looking to fill the void "Uncle Boy's" founder thought it would be great to open one that would serve the classic American cheeseburger with different variations and twists and that is when the journey began.
The  name "Uncle Boy's" is an homage to widely used nick name “boy” and “baby” for women in the Filipino community and it’s common knowledge within the community that  "every Filipino family has an uncle/tito boy and an aunty/tita baby" which is almost always true!

businessOwnerBio:
I love food and I love San Francisco. I started this business with no restaurant service experience and I have enjoyed the adventure while simultaneously feeling the pains of the journey on learning on the Job. Over all just here counting the little blessings that being a restauranteur brings. Specially thankful for our regulars who have been the sole reason we are still open today!

We choose and purchase salmon from difference ocean by season changes. We select the best quality salmon from Alaska, Scotland, Canada and Norway.

about_business:
speciality:
Original Joe's is a three-generation family owned and operated restaurant. Established over 80 years ago in 1937, Joe's is defined by quiet elegance, yet bustling with energy, affording a standard of excellence that enhances the total dining experience. Hospitality, familiarity, predictability--these are the key elements of the brand, providing guests with a sense of comfort upon first entering the lobby doors. The oldest of all the "Joe's" restaurants, Original Joe's is the innovator of the now nationally known "Joe's Concept"--exhibition-style kitchen, notable leather booths, smooth cocktails, and renowned Italian-American menu. The restaurant prepares dishes in an open kitchen for all to see, providing hearty portions at reasonable prices. Known as much for its comfortable familiarity as for its abundant portions, all menus feature a full selection of unpretentious, old-school dishes--from beef, veal, chicken, pasta and seafood, to more new-school specialty salads, appetizers, signature soups, and custom desserts.

historyText:
Original Joe's opened over 80 years ago in SF's Tenderloin District. Starting as a 14-stool counter, Joe's became a place where anyone, and everyone, could feel at home. Over the years, versions of "Joe's" restaurants opened in the Bay Area, but none possessed the character of the first. Original Joe's is the innovator of the now nationally known "Joe's Concept"-exhibition-style kitchen, notable leather booths, smooth cocktails & renowned Italian-American menu. After a fire destroyed the restaurant in 2007, the family reopened it in 2012 in a community that welcomed the rebirth of their grandfather's legacy. It now stands proud in the heart of SF's North Beach District--a mecca for natives, tourists & culinary aficionados alike. A now 3-generation family owned & operated business, Original Joe's has succeeded in establishing a high-profile identity in the Bay Area, standing tall amongst the well-known restaurants & bars--a sustainable business genuinely worthy of its proven credential.

about_business:
speciality:
At Big Fish House Omakase, our passion for perfection shines through in every detail. With meticulous dedication, our staff ensures a personalized experience, crafting a custom omakase menu that aligns precisely with your preferences. We source only the freshest, premium fish from Japan and beyond, expertly prepared by our skilled chefs using traditional techniques and innovative touches. Throughout your dining journey, we take every effort to ensure attentive service and a carefully curated ambiance to enhance your experience, leaving you with unforgettable memories of our exquisite seafood and unparalleled care.

historyText:
Big Fish House, established in 2022, is a renowned omakase restaurant in San Francisco. 
With over 30 years of experience in the Japanese restaurant industry, founder Julie Huang opened her first local restaurant, Kufuya, 23 years ago and takes great pride in providing the highest level of service combined with the freshest ingredients for her latest inspiration, Big Fish House Omakase. 

Directly importing fish from Japan, including uni, scallop, kinmedai, saba, kampachi, hamachi, and Shima-aji, Big Fish House ensures the freshest and highest quality sustainable ingredients. Inspired by world famous Omakase chef Kuo Zong Kun during her travels in Asia, Julie was inspired to share the sublime art of omakase to the San Francisco Bay Area, infusing custom, personalized culinary experiences into Big Fish restaurant's DNA. 

Today, Big Fish House is a testament to Julie's dedication, offering an unforgettable omakase journey showcasing the pinnacle of Japanese cuisine and sushi art. 

businessOwnerBio:
I've spent the last 30 years in the San Francisco restaurant industry and became inspired to bring authentic Japanese Omakase from Asia to my home in San Francisco. I love to serve creative, healthy, fresh and delicious food to my customers, treating them like they're a part of my family as they enjoy our immaculately crafted Omakase sushi & Japanese cuisine.

address: 22 Peace Plz Fl 2 San Francisco, CA 94115
about_business:
speciality:
Casual family-run restaurant with sushi, ramen, and a full menu of Japanese specialties. Try our innovative sushi rolls and reasonable priced combo meals!

At Kui Shin Bo in San Francisco Japantown, we pride ourselves in being an authentic Japanese restaurant with full menu of sushi, sashimi, ramen, as well as other Japanese specialties, with delivery and catering. Along with tried and true Japanese classics like and donburi, you can explore your palette by trying our innovative menu items such as our sushi burritos and okonomiyaki, a type of grilled savory pancake. If you're looking for a full Japanese dining experience in addition to sushi and ramen, try out our combo options when you dine at our San Francisco Japan Town Location. We also offer a catering program, so you can enjoy authentic Japanese food at home, at your events, or with groups, both large and small. Conveniently located on in Japan town walking distance to Union Street and Chestnut Street.

historyText:
Dedicated to an authentic Japanese culinary experience, the restaurant name kuishinbo meaning "a person who loves to eat" in Japanese, reflecting their commitment to deliver a completely satisfying dining experience, whether it is sushi, ramen, or shabu shabu. Whenever you find yourself in San Francisco, or need an authentic catering option, you can depend on us at Kui Shin Bo to indulge in your Japanese cuisine cravings.

Chef Clement's professional experience includes three years at Le Charm, a San Francisco bistro, one year at Elizabeth and Daniel, a 2001 James Beard nominated restaurant, and three years leading the kitchen at Fringale, a Basque inspired restaurant. He then opened his own restaurant, L'Ardoise Bistro in Mars 2008. L'Ardoise Bistro has been featured in the Michelin guide, and has a good rating in the Zagat Survey, yelp, and other blogs, plus a few article in the local papers.

Born in  the French Alps, Chef Clement then moved with his family in central France, and work at his father's butcher shop. He acquired a taste for fresh, simple food that makes the pride of his hometown's artisan products and his mother's home cooking.
Chef Clement began spending time in professional kitchens at age 15 and subsequently began his education by working in restaurants in Bordeaux, the Pyrenees and Paris.

historyText:
We think SF is ready for a fun, dynamic Thai food from regional cooking dishes to our grandma's recipes. 
Currently, we are offering many Northern Thai dishes from Chiangmai, Chiang Rai, and Loei. 

Chef/owner, "POP", is originally from Loei but spent most of his adulthood in Bangkok. Pop attributes his passion for food to his daily trips to the local market with his grandma. In which, a dish called "Panang Nuea" 24hrs braised Short ribs in panang spices and coconut milk reminiscent of his childhood where he cooked a large meal for his entire family.

Farmhouse Kitchen has been certified as a Thai Select restaurant, honoring its cooking which utilizes authentic Thai ingredients.

historyText:
In 2009, the owner Philip, a Puerto Rican New York native  was in Puerto Rico eating a plate of rice, beans, pork and mofongo and thought, "Why can't I find food like this in San Francisco?" So he called his cousin Gloria, a chef in San Juan, and together they created Parada 22. Parada 22 aims to recreate a classic Puerto Rican family meal, complete with Bomba y Plena music, laughter, and of course--Sangria!

about_business:
speciality:
We are a small locally owned seafood restaurant and fish market in the Castro. Owned and operated by the same owner since 1977, San Francisco's one-and-only Anchor Oyster Bar has been serving fresh sustainably caught fish, shellfish, crab, and delicious simply prepared seafood dishes for over 30 years.

Anchor serves the Bay Area's favorite clam chowder (San Francisco Chronicle) and the best oysters on the West coast (Coastal Living Magazine). Check us out on the third season of Check Please Bay Area!

historyText:
The storefront sits at the sleepy end of Castro Street. Roseann Grimm opened it in 1977 when the neighborhood was just finding its identity -- transitioning from Irish working-class holdout to gay mecca -- but she never catered to any one crowd. Grimm came from a long line of Italian fishermen, an oyster bar seemed like a natural choice.

"My grandparents ran an oyster house in North Beach, across from Enrico's, and I have pictures of all my uncles in front of our house on Fair Oaks with an ocean's worth of sea bass strung up," Grimm says.

Anchor's no-fuss interior -- a lunch counter and a handful of tables decorated with fishing photos of Grimm's Uncle Al -- echoes the food. While it's augmented by more adventurous daily specials, the menu has as its core straightforward piles of fresh crab, prawns, and shrimp served cocktail-style or on salads, and a thick, creamy, not too fishy New England clam chowder that has yet to meet its match anywhere in town.

name: Besharam
popular_dishes: Drunken Pani Puri, Maska Paneer, Dahi Wada, Pav Bhaji, Ringan No Oro, Sev Puri, Malai Kofta, Who Killed the Lamb, Fish Moilee, Kachori Dumplings, Saag Paneer, Mango Salad, Khichu, Khaman, Chole, Koftas, Andhra Fish Stew, Chili Garlic, Kanji Wada, Dabeli Paratha
about_business:
speciality:
We are a Chef-driven restaurant. This phrase is used often, so what do we mean when we use that here at Besharam? The food curated by Chef Heena is a reflection and homage to her journey and struggles that brought her here. Often when food from other cultures has a "twist" on it, it is referred to as "fusion." We openly reject that description and do not identify as a fusion restaurant. Rather than dilute our food for certain palates, each dish reflects a story, an experience, a place (or several) from Mumbai, to the UK, to the Bay Area. It is her mother's kitchen and Mumbai streets. It is California produce and the foods she invented for her children's immigrant lives. It is techniques she has acquired with spices that she brings with her. As the Chef says "I'm not your mom, so don't expect me to cook like her."

historyText:
Heena joined Bay Area incubator kitchen La Cocina, in 2014, with a vision for a mobile food business. After a transformative dinner at State Bird Provisions, she altered her vision permanently. She realized there were chefs who cooked what they wanted, and ungoverned by simple provenance, they treated ingredients with care. "I want to cook food like that," she thought, and at the 2016 La Cocina conference, in a panel of her peers, she declared that intent; to open a fine dining restaurant that shared her journey, her food, her point of view. In July 2019, Chef Heena and Paresh re-launched Besharam, after taking on full-ownership of the restaurant. Chef Heena has reclaimed her restaurant after a year of partnership and personifying the meaning of Besharam with a new attitude, dishes, and cocktails to show the community her creativity and technical culinary expertise. Grounded in traditional Gujarati food, the dishes on her new menu are meant to embody culture and hospitality.

businessOwnerBio:
Chef Heena started cooking professionally late in life. She was always told her goals were too besharam, an Urdu word for shameless that is often used in South Asian culture as an insult, a label for a woman who dares to do things not considered "respectful" or "appropriate." While Heena cultivated her distinct style over five years at La Cocina, a culinary incubator in San Francisco which provides resources to entrepreneurs with an emphasis on working class women and immigrant communities, her food narrates her diaspora and experiences living around the world. At La Cocina, Heena's soulful dishes, unmistakably hers, won the hearts of Bay Area chefs and luminaries such as Traci Des Jardins of Jardiniere, and Stuart Brioza & Nicole Krasinski of State Bird Provisions and The Progress, through collaborative pop-ups. As Heena says, "I want to always be asking, are you Besharam enough? Where have you been holding back, and what more could you be doing?"

historyText:
MaMo is the only restaurant in San Francisco, featuring Californian cuisine with a Colombian & Venezuelan flair.  MAMO's concept is the fusion of the exotic tropical flavors of South America, with the sophisticated taste of California.
 
Inspired by the concept of diversity, our promise to our guests is to provide a cozy, yet chic environment, where they can experience the combination of cultures that the San Francisco Bay Area offers.
 
MaMo, was born when owners M & M decided to share a bit of their own culture with San Francisco and bring the flavors of Colombia & Venezuelan cuisine to the Marina District scene; using, and offering some of our best Californian products and combining them with local Beers & a Great Wine Selection! 
​

businessOwnerBio:
Michael and Milena are the owners of MaMo. Milena is from Caracas Venezuela and Michael from Bogota Colombia. More than a decade after moving to California and searching constantly for a place that will offer a culinary taste of their homeland, they decided to open MaMo to share some of their culture with the San Francisco scene.

speciality:
We specialize in making beef bone broth ramen with black truffle and olives. Our menu special includes beef bone marrow and ox tail ramen. As well as tsukemen, ramen with dipping broth on the side. As ramen lovers, we are trying to offer something different than what people usually find in restaurants which are mainly pork and chicken broth.

historyText:
Ushi Taro began as my partner and I decided to bring something different to the ramen scene in Bay Area. It took us more than half year to find the location and trying to make the ramen taste the way we wanted, we also tried many ingredients before we decided which ones go into the broth and on top of our ramen. As we opened the restaurant in June 2018, we have learned a lot more while serving customers, and we will keeping learning and improving as we go. We really appreciate your business and input to make Ushi Taro better. Thank you!

about_business:
speciality:
The two hope to bring reasonably-priced Italian meals--with an authentic Italian vibe--to the area. And true to the family-friendly spirit of Italian eateries, the restaurant was created with both parents and their children in mind.

historyText:
Roma Antica was born in the heart of the Marina District. The product of a rich cultural heritage that passed along for generations, the art of Roman Cuisine, revisited in a modern style.

We aim through our cuisine to share our family tradition, surrounding you with a simple meal in great company. The menu offers a selection of authentic recipes from Rome as well as additional specialties from the magic of sitting around a table, sipping good wine and enjoy all the regions of Italy.

All of this, wrapped in a true Italian accent, will make you feel as if you were living a typical day in Rome, where "the sun kisses you, the wind caresses you and the city protects you!

The partners are Dogukan Solmaz  and Roberto Sbaraglia, a Roman whose father has owned a restaurant in Rome, Antica, for the past 30 years
The two met at hospitality school in Rome in 2005 and have been looking for a place in San Francisco for the past three years.

Vast California wine list and full bar with premium liquor historyText: Fog Harbor Fish House offers the quintessential San Francisco waterfront dining experience. Steeped in tradition, Fog Harbor Fish House was created by the original developers of PIER 39 and is filled with a quarter century of San Francisco history. Family-owned and operated, Fog Harbor Fish House is among the most favored restaurants on the Wharf where we pride ourselves in offering the freshest seafood in San Francisco. businessOwnerBio: Bob Partrite is the Chief Operating Officer of the Simco Restaurant group on Pier 39. He is passionate about serving fresh sustainable seafood and creating a dining experience that is memorable. His goal is to exceed guests expectations and you will find him in our restaurants on a daily basis. "We are your local PIER 39 restaurant, come visit us and see why".

Warren Simmons was the visionary behind the creation, conceptualizing and development of what would become one of the world's most famous landmarks: PIER 39. Today, over 30 years later, Simco Restaurants continues to own and operate the most successful restaurants on Fisherman's Wharf including the award-winning Pier Market Restaurant, Fog Harbor Fish House, Wipeout Bar & Grill, Eagle Cafe and Biscoff Coffee Corner.

about_business:
speciality:
Our margaritas are made with 100% blue agave tequilas. We hope our homemade infusions make for a unique experience. Our passion is all agave spirits. We have curated a list that will cure all your worries. Traditional Michoacán carnitas, Pulpo al Pastor, and Tinga Flautas are just a few of the dishes you can expect from our menu.

historyText:
The story begins in a small village outside of San Felipe, Guanajuato, located in the heart of Mexico, called El Varal, where I was raised by my grandparents, Mama Emilia and Papa Reyes. I wanted to honor my childhood in El Varal with the perfect unity of Mama Emilia's healing through plants and prayer and Papa Reyes' gift in captivating the true essence of the agave, something tequila, mezcal, or sotol will never do. Here at Santería, we have started our quest in reverse, into the beginning of this incredible story of maguey by adding an intentional element of healing and tradition into every dish and cocktail.

Owned and operated by the husband-and-wife team of Mike and Kristen McCaffery, Mr. Digby's is the newest addition to Noe Valley!

Mr. Digby was the family's Old English Sheepdog. Due to his friendly and gentle demeanor and his propensity to wait on the front lawn for his owners to come home from school, Digby soon became a staple in his neighborhood. Friends and strangers alike knew him by name. Mr. Digby embodies the spirit of our new restaurant - a neighborhood staple where we know each other by name. We look forward to welcoming you to Mr. Digby's.

You can also join us at our sister restaurant, NOVY!

This is our first brick and mortar. The restaurant is dedicated to providing an intimate dining experience like no other in the city focused on crafting a unique tasting menu inspired by ramen, the techniques, and philosophy.

name: Lokma
popular_dishes: Turkish Breakfast For 2, Manti, Sunrise Combo, Papas Bravas, Menemen, Creamy Mushroom Soup, Calamari, Short Rib, Grilled Chicken, Breakfast Sandwich, Zucchini Dolmas, Chicken Sandwich, Trio Spreads, Presidio Salad, Branzino, Tzatziki, Turlu Omelet, Bal & Kaymak, Grilled Lamb Kofte, Baklava
about_business:
speciality: We at Lokma are striving to serve a fresh and colorful creation of Californian and Turkish fare while serving our guests with warm hospitality in our bright and open space. We are interested in growing towards new and interesting ways to join food cultures, forming solid relationships with our neighbors and providing a delightful and pleasant environment. historyText: Lokma, which means "a bite" in Turkish, opened in Feb 2018 and is located in the Outer Richmond. We serve a fresh Californian and Turkish fare while serving our guests with warm hospitality in our bright and open space. We are very excited to meet you. businessOwnerBio: Lokma founded by  Emre Kabayel and Neslihan Demirtas.  

Kabayel’s degree in electrical engineering from Turkey, he decided to enroll College to sharpen his communication skills and to take classes in business administration. After completing a certificate program, he took a job at Kitchen Istanbul, a Turkish rest. He worked his way through a number of jobs and discovered that he really loved the restaurant business.

Ms. Demirtas has substantive experience in finance and educational background in Economics and Business. She is equipped with the academic and professional expertise needed to manage the financials restaurant business.

Kabayel and Demirtas were eager to introduce people to other Turkish dishes in addition to the popular and more familiar kababs, gyros and flat breads. Their families back in Turkey helped them put together their menu and once set, they trained their chef to prepare the dishes, which they continue to experiment with and perfect.
